    "recap_headline": "Rutgers University",
    "recap_text": "PISCATAWAY, N.J. \u2013\nRutgers baseball cruised to a 13-3 victory over Monmouth on Tuesday afternoon, winning the midweek showdown in seven-inning, run-rule fashion.\nThe Scarlet Knights (12-8) collected 13 runs on 10 hits and seven walks, beating the Hawks\u00a0(8-9) to wrap up a 10-game homestand in the win column.\nPeyton Bonds\nhit a home run and had four RBIs, while\nCharlie Meglio\nhit a two-run homer and\nTrey Wells\n,\nMatt Chatelle\nand\nChase Krewson\nall collected multiple hits.\nOn the mound,\nJacob Pedersen\nwas dominant with five shutout innings, striking out six with no walks and earning the victory.\nThanks to the offensive outburst, Pedersen and starter\nHenry Radbill\n(2.0 IP) were the only two pitchers RU needed to use.\nMeglio's two-run homer in the first gave the Scarlet Knights an early cushion. Krewson followed with an RBI single in the third and Bonds added a two-run home run to push the lead to 5-0.\nDespite Monmouth adding three in the third, RU responded with one in the bottom half on a sac fly and another two in the sixth on a sac fly and an error.\nIn the bottom of the seventh, the Scarlet Knights bats added five to walk it off. Krewson singled in one,\nJulius Rosado\nand Bonds both drew bases-loaded walks and\nYomar Carreras\nand Wells each had a run-scoring fielder's choice\u00a0to make it 13-3 and end the game in seven.\nRutgers returns to action this weekend in conference play, hitting the road to take on Illinois with game one set for 7 p.m. Friday.\nFollow Rutgers Baseball on Social Media\nX\n|\nInstagram\n|\nFacebook"
